# graphify knowledge graph.
# Committed: graph.json + GRAPH_REPORT.md. The semantic layer in graph.json (INFERRED
# edges, hyperedges, community names) comes from an LLM — it costs minutes to rebuild and
# is not reproducible, so a fresh clone must inherit it rather than regenerate it.
# Everything else is local state: cache/ and the dated backup dirs are artifacts, and
# manifest.json stores per-file mtimes, which git does not preserve — committing it would
# churn on every clone.
/graphify-out/*
!/graphify-out/graph.json
!/graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md
